first three songs blend together into one long song , three songs middle break up monotony some soft acoustic numbers which seem rather long , then heaviness continues like it various interludes . while it sounds rather unfulfilling first listen , album grows you when you learn appreciate what it offer . bottom line : definitely better than most what victory records puts out market , strangely enough one least publicized their roster . if you're fan mathcore or metal general , you'll probably find something this album you like . this album brings shining ray hope hopeless genre . track selections : " lost perfection : coulrophobia " , " mordecai , " " ad dglgmut " 8/1
